entries.title: Your Tuesday Briefing: A Bombing in Pakistan
entries.description: Also, Israel attacks Iran and the Adani Group fights fraud allegations.

entries.title: Netherlands and Japan Said to Join U.S. in Curbing China’s Access to Chip Tech
entries.description: A new agreement is expected to expand the reach of U.S. technology restrictions on China issued last year.

entries.title: The Double Whammy Making Italy the West’s Fasting Shrinking Nation
entries.description: Italy’s population of elder Italians is soaring as its birthrate plummets, putting the country at the forefront of a global demographic trend that experts call the “silver tsunami.”

entries.title: Golf Course or Housing? A Patch of Green Divides Hong Kong
entries.description: The dispute over the city’s golf club exposes rare political friction for the elite in the new Hong Kong, where the establishment is torn between defending wealth and following Beijing’s wishes.

entries.title: NATO’s Chief Hints That South Korea Should Consider Military Aid to Ukraine
entries.description: NATO’s secretary-general, Jens Stoltenberg, urged South Korea to increase its support for Ukraine in the face of Russia’s invasion.

entries.title: Turkey Raises Fresh Objections to Sweden and Finland’s NATO Bids
entries.description: As he faces a tough fight for re-election, President Recep Tayyip Erdogan of Turkey has been raising fresh objections to Sweden and Finland’s NATO membership bids.

entries.title: Boris Johnson Claims Putin Threatened to Fire a Missile at Him
entries.description: The former British prime minister said the Russian leader made the remark during a phone call in the weeks before Putin’s forces invaded Ukraine.

entries.title: Ukraine Calls for Allies to Speed Up Weapons Deliveries
entries.description: President Volodymyr Zelensky of Ukraine asked allies to quickly supply pledged armaments and ‘new necessary weaponry.’

entries.title: Beyond the Border
entries.description: How the migrant surge is playing out far from the Southern U.S.

entries.title: Blast at Pakistan Mosque Kills At Least 27
entries.description: The explosion came in a highly secured part of Peshawar, a provincial capital. It was the worst attack in the country in months.

entries.title: Blinken to Meet Netanyahu at Turbulent Moment for Israel
entries.description: The secretary of state will sit down with the Israeli prime minister as violence and mass protests rattle his country.

entries.title: Baghdad Loses Green Space to Real Estate Boom
entries.description: The problem is driving up temperatures in what is already one of the hottest cities in the world, where air-conditioning is a luxury only the rich can afford.

entries.title: Some Wagner Convict Fighters in Ukraine Are Returning to Russia
entries.description: Tens of thousands of inmates have joined a mercenary group fighting with the Kremlin’s decimated forces in Ukraine. Some of them are returning to civilian life with military training and, in many cases, battlefield traumas.

entries.title: Gandhi’s Life in Photos, 75 Years After His Assassination
entries.description: Known as the father of Indian independence, his concept of nonviolent resistance to fight injustice has inspired political movements around the world.

entries.title: Your Monday Briefing
entries.description: A wave of violence in Israel and the West Bank.

entries.title: ‘Squid Game’ Actor Oh Young-soo Goes on Trial on Sex Crime Charges on Feb. 3
entries.description: Oh Young-soo, the actor who portrayed a contestant in the popular Netflix series, is accused of inappropriately touching a South Korean woman in 2017.

entries.title: Israel Launched Drone Attack on Iranian Facility, Officials Say
entries.description: While the target’s purpose is unclear, the city of Isfahan is a major center of Iranian missile production, research and development.
